{
  "stem": "17299.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 216.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then the Jewish police had to pull the chair from under the feet of the person who got hanged.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Every one.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Every execution I witnessed, shooting or hanging.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first mass execution I ever witnessed was middle of May 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were-- 15 Jews were brought in a camp. 15 or 16, I'm not sure of that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one of them got pulled up on the gallows.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was a Jew who had two stars on his clothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One in front and one in back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We found out later on that he was a Latvian Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then 14 had to line up in one row.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then the SS walked behind them and shot them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now comes the worst part.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "One of the Jews, 14 or 15 year old boy named Frank-- he was from the [INAUDIBLE] of Dusseldorf-- let himself drop to the ground when the order came, fire.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a fellow Jew named [INAUDIBLE] Wertheim-- we thought he was a hero when he opposed Lange to select Jews for an execution-- pointed out to the SS that this one had not been shot.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The SS put him on his feet, and they shot him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the majority of those who got executed were still alive, moving arms and legs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the SS walked between them and shot everyone who was moving.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the last execution was-- for illegal food-- was in June 1942.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were also two from Hanover.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] because I had to bury them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] in the meantime, also, came the order any Jew who doesn't-- is unable to work-- will get only half the ration of bread.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they enforced that, even though there was no roll call who would go to work or not.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
